    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="596"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/208</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 924</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department’s telegram No.
                    925, March 28, 6 p.m., relative to the objection raised by the French Government
                    to Article 10 of the law governing the Mexican bank of issue, I have the honor
                    to report that it is apparent that nothing may be accomplished at this time by
                    individual or joint protest, and for this reason I suggest that no
                    representations be made at present.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry P. Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
